com.facebook.react

Class CompositeReactPackage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.react.ReactInstancePackage
      • com.facebook.react.CompositeReactPackage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReactPackage, ViewManagerOnDemandReactPackage

    public class CompositeReactPackage
extends ReactInstancePackage
implements ViewManagerOnDemandReactPackage
    CompositeReactPackage allows to create a single package composed of views and modules from several other packages.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CompositeReactPackage

        public CompositeReactPackage(ReactPackage arg1,
                             ReactPackage arg2,
                             ReactPackage... args)
        The order in which packages are passed matters. It may happen that a NativeModule or or a ViewManager exists in two or more ReactPackages. In that case the latter will win i.e. the latter will overwrite the former. This re-occurrence is detected by comparing a name of a module.
